  "response": "The most important question to ask can vary greatly depending on context, but a fundamental one that often resonates across different situations is: \"What truly matters to me?\" This question encourages self-reflection and helps define priorities, values, and goals, guiding decisions in personal life, relationships, and career. Other contexts might lead to different critical questions, such as \"How can I contribute to a better world?\" in a social context or \"What do I need to learn or understand to move forward?\" in a professional setting.",
